article.headline: Cornell 55, Princeton 35
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Ryan Wittman had 17 points and Louis Dale had 14 points and six rebounds to lead Cornell to a 55-35 win over Princeton Saturday night in the Ivy League. Cornell (8-8, 1-1) shot 55.6 percent from the field while holding Princeton (9-6, 0-2) to 30.4 percent. Princeton was leading, 14-13, early in the first half until Dale sunk a 3-pointer to give the Big Red the edge for good. Cornell built its lead to 27-16 by halftime, and the gap continued to grow in the second period. Zach Finley led Princeton with 12 points, and was the only player to score in the double digits for the Tigers. Luke Owings and Marcus Schroeder each added seven points for Princeton.
